article.headline: Austin Peay 74, Evansville 71
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Landon Shipley scored a career-high 24 points as Austin Peay withstood a late rally and beat Evansville 74-71 Wednesday. Evansville (4-4) led 66-64 with 3:37 left on a jump shot by Kyle Anslinger, who had 13 points. A 3-point shot by Maurice Hampton with 2:39 put Austin Peay (6-4) up 67-66, and the Governors never lost the lead. Austin Peay sealed the win with a jump shot by Drake Reed and five free throws by Shipley, Hampton and Zac Schlader. Austin Peay led 43-35 at the half. Hampton scored 19 and Reed added another 10 and had 13 rebounds. For the Aces, Bradley Strickland had 16 points. Matt Webster added another 16 points, along with nine rebounds. There were five ties.
